---
import '../../styles/global.css';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const title = "The Modern Dev Stack: GitHub, Vercel, and Cursor Explained | Singing River AI";
const description = "A beginner-friendly guide to modern web development tools. Learn how GitHub, Vercel, and Cursor work together to build and deploy websites faster.";
const canonicalURL = new URL(Astro.url.pathname, Astro.site);
const publishDate = "2024-12-20";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "BlogPosting",
      "headline": "The Modern Dev Stack: GitHub, Vercel, and Cursor Explained",
      "description": description,
      "datePublished": publishDate,
      "dateModified": publishDate,
      "wordCount": 1400,
      "articleSection": "Development",
      "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Todd Frederickson" },
      "publisher": { "@id": "https://singingriverai.com/#organization" },
      "mainEntityOfPage": { "@id": canonicalURL.href }
    },
    {
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://singingriverai.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Blog", "item": "https://singingriverai.com/blog/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Modern Web Development Stack" }
      ]
    }
  ]
};
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="canonical" href={canonicalURL} />
    <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:type" content="article" />
    <meta name="robots" content="index, follow" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
  </head>
  <body class="grain-overlay">
    <Header />
    <main>
      <article class="pt-32 pb-20">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
          <!-- Header -->
          <nav class="mb-8" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
            <ol class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-stone">
              <li><a href="/" class="hover:text-accent transition-colors">Home</a></li>
              <li><span class="mx-2">/</span></li>
              <li><a href="/blog" class="hover:text-accent transition-colors">Blog</a></li>
              <li><span class="mx-2">/</span></li>
              <li class="text-charcoal font-medium">Modern Web Development Stack</li>
            </ol>
          </nav>

          <div class="mb-8">
            <span class="text-sm text-accent font-medium uppercase tracking-wider">Development</span>
            <h1 class="heading-display text-4xl md:text-5xl mt-4 mb-4">
              The Modern Dev Stack: GitHub, Vercel, and <em>Cursor Explained</em>
            </h1>
            <p class="text-stone">December 20, 2024 · 7 min read</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Content -->
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
            <p class="text-xl text-stone leading-relaxed">
              If you've worked with a web developer recently, you've probably heard terms like GitHub, Vercel, and maybe even Cursor. Here's what these tools actually do and why they matter for your business website.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-display text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">GitHub: Your Code's Home Base</h2>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <strong>What it is:</strong> GitHub is where your website's code lives. Think of it as a sophisticated Google Drive for code—but with superpowers.
            </p>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <strong>Why it matters:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-stone mb-6">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Version history:</strong> Every change is saved. If something breaks, you can instantly roll back to a working version</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Collaboration:</strong> Multiple developers can work on the same project without stepping on each other's toes</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Ownership:</strong> You own your code. If you change developers, your project transfers cleanly</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <strong>Business takeaway:</strong> Always ask developers to use GitHub (or similar) for your projects. You should have access to the repository. This protects your investment.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-display text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">Vercel: From Code to Live Website</h2>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <strong>What it is:</strong> Vercel is a hosting platform that automatically turns your code into a live website. When you push changes to GitHub, Vercel detects them and deploys your updated site within seconds.
            </p>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <strong>Why it matters:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-stone mb-6">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Speed:</strong> Vercel's global network serves your site from locations closest to your visitors. Fast sites rank better on Google</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Preview deployments:</strong> See changes on a test URL before they go live. Perfect for approving updates</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Instant rollbacks:</strong> If something goes wrong, one click reverts to the previous version</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>SSL included:</strong> Free security certificates, so your site shows as secure (https://)</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <strong>Business takeaway:</strong> Vercel (and similar platforms like Netlify) give you professional-grade hosting without managing servers. Updates are instant and rollbacks are painless.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-display text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">Cursor: The AI-Powered Code Editor</h2>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <strong>What it is:</strong> Cursor is a code editor with AI built-in. It's like having an experienced developer looking over your shoulder, ready to help write code, explain things, and catch errors.
            </p>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <strong>Why it matters:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-stone mb-6">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Faster development:</strong> AI helps write boilerplate code, suggests completions, and catches bugs early</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Built-in chat:</strong> Ask questions about your code, get explanations, request changes in natural language</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Multi-model support:</strong> Use Claude, GPT-4, or other AI models depending on the task</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <strong>Business takeaway:</strong> Developers using AI-powered tools like Cursor can work faster, which means lower costs and faster turnaround for your projects.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-display text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">How They Work Together</h2>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Here's the typical workflow for a modern website:
            </p>
            <ol class="space-y-4 text-stone mb-6">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <span class="font-display text-accent text-xl">1.</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Code in Cursor:</strong> Developer writes and edits code with AI assistance
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <span class="font-display text-accent text-xl">2.</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Push to GitHub:</strong> Changes are saved with a description of what changed
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <span class="font-display text-accent text-xl">3.</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Vercel deploys:</strong> Automatically builds and publishes the updated site
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <span class="font-display text-accent text-xl">4.</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Preview and approve:</strong> Client reviews on a preview URL before going live
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <span class="font-display text-accent text-xl">5.</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Live in seconds:</strong> Once approved, the production site updates instantly
                </div>
              </li>
            </ol>

            <h2 class="heading-display text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">What This Means for Your Business</h2>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              This modern stack offers several advantages over traditional website development:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-stone mb-6">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Faster updates:</strong> Changes can go live in minutes, not days</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Lower risk:</strong> Version control and instant rollbacks mean mistakes are easily fixed</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Better performance:</strong> Global CDN hosting makes your site fast for all visitors</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Transparency:</strong> You can see every change, when it was made, and by whom</span>
              </li>
            </ul>

            <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-8 mt-12">
              <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-4">Questions About Modern Web Development?</h3>
              <p class="text-stone mb-4">
                Whether you're building a new website or modernizing an existing one, we can help you understand your options and make the right technology choices.
              </p>
              <a href="/#contact" class="btn-primary inline-flex">
                <span>Let's Talk</span>
              </a>
            </div>

            <!-- Related Posts -->
            <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-stone/20">
              <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-6">Related Articles</h3>
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <a href="/blog/claude-code-for-developers/" class="group">
                  <div class="bg-cream rounded-xl p-4">
                    <span class="text-sm text-accent">Development</span>
                    <h4 class="font-display text-lg mt-1 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">Claude Code for Developers: AI-Powered Development</h4>
                  </div>
                </a>
                <a href="/blog/ai-for-seo-rankings/" class="group">
                  <div class="bg-cream rounded-xl p-4">
                    <span class="text-sm text-accent">SEO</span>
                    <h4 class="font-display text-lg mt-1 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">AI for SEO: How to Use AI for Better Rankings</h4>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
